=== Dataset License (datasets/, sample_substitute_corpus/) ===

Cooperative Defensive Patent Pledge (#2260)

The canonical datasets in this pack (corpus files, sealed question banks, benchmark
results) are released under the Cooperative Defensive Patent Pledge:

1. You may use, reproduce, modify, and distribute these datasets for any purpose,
   including commercial purposes, subject to the conditions below.

2. If you use these datasets in published research, you must cite the K528 benchmark
   report and this pack per the format in CITATION.md.

3. You may NOT use these datasets to file or support patent claims that would restrict
   other cooperative platforms, academic researchers, or non-profit organizations from
   using the architectures, methodologies, or findings described herein.

4. The Cooperative Defensive Patent Pledge does not limit your right to assert patents
   against conventional technology companies that are not cooperative platforms and that
   use the architectures or methodologies described herein without contributing to the
   cooperative commons.

5. The Acme Cooperative sample corpus (sample_substitute_corpus/) is dedicated to the
   public domain (CC0). All data therein is fictitious. No copyright claimed.

=== Member-Data Sovereignty Guarantee ===

No terms in this license restrict your sovereign right to substitute your own corpus
for the canonical corpus and keep your data, your questions, and your benchmark results
entirely on your own machine. The sovereignty contract documented in SUBSTITUTION_GUIDE.md
is a design constraint, not a license condition — it holds regardless of which license
tier applies to the code or datasets you use.

